Records, Universal/Republic in the U.S., and Positiva in the U.K. The album is renowned for its blend of Eurodance and trance styles, characterized by catchy melodies and synth-driven beats. Who Needs Guitars Anyway? remains a quintessential Eurodance album, capturing the essence of late 1990s and early 2000s electronic music. <a href=\"https://www.last.fm/music/Alice+Deejay/Who+Needs+Guitars+Anyway%3F\">Read more on Last.fm</a>.","content":"“Who Needs Guitars Anyway?” is the debut and only studio album by Dutch electronic music group Alice Deejay, released on March 28, 2000, through Violent Records, Universal/Republic in the U.S., and Positiva in the U.K.  The album is renowned for its blend of Eurodance and trance styles, characterized by catchy melodies and synth-driven beats. Who Needs Guitars Anyway? remains a quintessential Eurodance album, capturing the essence of late 1990s and early 2000s electronic music. <a href=\"https://www.last.fm/music/Alice+Deejay/Who+Needs+Guitars+Anyway%3F\">Read more on Last.fm</a>. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License; additional terms may apply."}}}